<h1>EXECUTIVE SUMMARY</h1>
<p><strong>Client:</strong> Sir Jerome<br>
<strong>Project:</strong> Infinity Finance (LoanBrick) LMS<br>
<strong>Date:</strong> March 20, 2026</p>

<h2>1. Project Health & Accomplishments</h2>
<p>The LoanBrick Lending Management System is currently <strong>95% complete</strong>. The critical infrastructure, core lending logic, offline-first mobile synchronization, and financial reporting (MFI KPIs) have been successfully developed, tested, and implemented.</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Offline-First Mobile App:</strong> Robust synchronization utilizing WatermelonDB and Supabase, enabling field collectors to record payments in areas with zero internet connectivity.</li>
    <li><strong>Core Lending Engine:</strong> Automated amortization scheduling, loan disbursements, payment allocations, and loan renewal logic.</li>
    <li><strong>Security & Encryption:</strong> Critical PII (Personally Identifiable Information) such as phone numbers, addresses, and bank accounts are encrypted at rest on the local devices.</li>
    <li><strong>Financial & KPI Analytics:</strong> Executive dashboards featuring Portfolio at Risk (PAR), Operating Self-Sufficiency (OSS), Income Statements, and Balance Sheets.</li>
    <li><strong>Digital Passbook:</strong> Borrower-facing digital ledgers with PDF export capabilities.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Next Phase: System Data Migration (1-Week Sprint)</h2>
<div class="highlight">
    <p>To transition from active development to production, the next critical phase is the <strong>System Data Migration</strong>, scheduled to take place over a 1-week period.</p>
</div>

<h3>Scope of Migration: Weekly Borrowers</h3>
<p>The primary focus of this migration sprint is the onboarding of all active <strong>Weekly Borrowers</strong>.</p>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Data Cleansing & Formatting:</strong> Formatting the existing historical data (from Excel/CSV or legacy systems) into the database schema format.</li>
    <li><strong>Borrower Profile Import:</strong> Bulk creation of encrypted borrower identities, assigning route indexes, and mapping them to designated collectors.</li>
    <li><strong>Active Loan Porting:</strong> Importing active loan contracts, including outstanding principal balances, accrued interest, and remaining terms.</li>
    <li><strong>Historical Payment Seeding:</strong> Injecting historical payment logs to ensure accurate initial balances and correct Portfolio at Risk (PAR) metrics from Day 1.</li>
    <li><strong>Reconciliation:</strong> Cross-referencing the migrated database totals against legacy system totals to guarantee 100% financial accuracy.</li>
</ol>

